      section
        h2.title ANZAC
        p This work for orchestra and nine soloists is a personal reflection on the ANZAC phenomenon. The nine soloists, supported by the orchestra, may be seen as suggesting characters, moods, images, or memories, in dream-like references to confusion, nostalgia, ceremony and contradiction. 
        p The work is in two parts, each having a number of continuous sections. Here they are, with (in brackets) the soloists featured.
        ul.accordion
          li
            span.accordion__title Part 1
            .accordion__hidden
              ul
                li Dawn (Trumpet, all soloists)
                li Fearful (Violin, Cello)
                li Thoughtful (Clarinet, Guitar)
                li Apprehensive (Clarinet, Piano, Guitar)
                li Nostalgic (Violin)

          li
            span.accordion__title Part 2
            .accordion__hidden
